France and the rest of Europe in the focus of investors.
On Tuesday, a statistical storm was blowing through Europe.
The individual countries published their data on GDP for the third quarter.
The Czech economy stagnated compared to the previous quarter, with Germany and France growing.
But the bond market is breaking all records today.
Investors not only keep an eye on Greece, but also on Spain, France, Austria and other countries.
