The Saturday talk, filled with information about figure types, was spiced up by three visitors from the industry:
Stylist Jan Pokorný, fashion designer Jakub Polanka and fashion photographer Ben Renč.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is illusion and that a stylist should be able to take advantage of it.
And sent in stylist can work with a single piece of clothing in quite different ways.
The magic word is variability.
For example, you can wear a trench coat over the jeans as usual, like a t-shirt or coat, but you can also wear it on the naked body, put heels on it and wear it as a dress.
It's enough to roll up the sleeves or collar and the whole look looks completely different.
"Play with it," he stressed.
