"Only then can you hurt her," Jakub said.
Finally, I realize why we have to worry about all these doctrines, what you can combine with what and why, even if you often get to see very different things in fashion journals.
Not to mention fashion shows.
Thanks to photographer Ben, I now know that a stylist must have prepared a lot more clothing variants than he ultimately photographed.
So you have to be prepared for a fashion story with ten pages (i.e. ten outfits) to style at least fifteen.
And also that the clothing in the photo in combination with other accessories sometimes looks quite different than in reality.
So you have to reckon with all this when designing the outfit.
Jan Pokorný confirmed that image and styl sometimes make up half of the success.
You only need to look at Madonna, a not exactly brilliant singer, from whom image and marketing have made a world star.
