However, the player encounters news in the movements, the environment, the disguises and the enemies - and a "playable" Luigi.
Colom guarantees the delivery of Portillos to the United States
The President of Guatemala, Álvaro Colom, announced this Tuesday that he would allow the extradition of former Governor Alfonso Portillo to be responsible in the United States for the US $70 million money-laundering conspiracy.
This is how the US's request to extradite Portillo ends so that it can be brought to justice there.
In a press conference, Colom confirmed that his decision was based on the independence of judicial authority and government, taking into account that a decision-making court had already ordered extradition.
He stressed that he had not interfered with court decisions during his government and had granted all the extradition requests he had been informed of.
Besides Portillo, Sergio Ruano Marroquín is extradited for murder and serious assault, Edgar Estrada Morales and Víctor Estrada Paredes, both for drug trafficking.
The action taken by Colom is a government act which takes place when all judicial and constitutional authorities are exhausted to condemn the former President of the State (2000-2004).
According to the decisions of the Fifth Criminal Court and the Guatemalan Constitutional Court, Portillo must be extradited if its legal situation in Guatemala is clarified and its human rights guaranteed.
Portillo was acquitted for embezzlement of 120 million Quetzales in the Ministry of Defense during his reign. This trial was preceded by extradition, but the minister objected and revived the case anew.
Trinijove helped 6000 young people threatened by social exclusion
The organisation was set up to prevent the marginalisation of young people without vocational training.
The first 25 years of life of the welfare organization Trinijove have led to important results: in this quarter of a century, 6000 young people threatened with social exclusion were supported to find a way out of their difficult situation.
In addition, there are over a hundred jobs created for this social group.
On the occasion of the anniversary, an event was held yesterday in the former factory buildings of Fabra i Coats, in which more than 300 people participated.
Trinijove was established in 1986 in Trinitat Vella with the aim of helping young people with low levels of education, without work, with drug problems at risk of marginality.
Yesterday's celebration in Sant Andreu was attended by many officials from institutions and institutions who have worked with the association over the past 25 years.
The participation of political representatives from different directions during election campaigns demonstrated the impartiality of the work done by Trinijove.
In addition to the President of the Generalitat (Parliament of the Autonomous Region of Catalonia), Artur Mas, and his predecessor Jordi Pujol participated in the celebrations of the former Socialist Minister of Education Ernest Maragall and the former mayor and now left-green city councillor Ricard Goma.
The large hall of Fabra i Coats was also visited by the current Catalan Minister for Social Affairs and the Family, Josep Lluís Cleries, and Jaume Lanaspa, Director General of the Social Fund of the Sparkasse La Caixa.
Mas stressed that Trinijove was born in very difficult times and that today's times are no less complicated, but he added that the work done so far is "a good basis".
For the President of Generalitat, Trinijove is an example that knows how to fight difficult circumstances and gives hope to people in difficulty.
"The economic crisis is nothing new for the association and the work it does," he said.
Occupied house where huge parties were held was cleared
The owners had occupied 11 of the 13 apartments in the building on the street Balmes No. 51 (Barcelona).
The twelve squatters left the building yesterday afternoon without resisting.
Everything points out that the nightmares of the neighbors of House No. 51 on the street Balmes have come to an end.
Twelve people left yesterday at noon voluntarily the building, which they illegally occupied and in which they had organized huge festivals, which had driven the neighborhood to despair. The evacuation took place by judicial order without police intervention.
After the evacuation, the door lock was changed to avoid a similar situation.
"From now on, the access will be controlled," the house manager confirmed.
The squatters, who had occupied 11 of the 13 apartments of the building - the rest were inhabited - took the entire electrical plant and part of the water supply with them. In addition, they had painted the walls and left behind all kinds of garbage, especially cans with alcoholic beverages.
In the three lower floors huge parties were celebrated, which lasted up to two days and drove the tenants to despair.
Next to the building is a discotheque, Balmes 51, which also suffered damage.
Her owner, Maria Pantinat, explained to Europa Press that her business had fallen by 80% since the beginning of the occupation.
The owner of the disco pointed out that the squatters made their unfair competition, because they sold the drinks for three euros, while they cost 10 euros in the disco.
In addition, the owner of the leisure area had been reported by the neighbors because of restlessness, while according to her statement the noise did not come from the visitors of the disco, but from the squatters and in particular from the guests of the festivals that were organized there, and which, according to the angry neighbours, became more and more and more longer in the last weeks.
The discotheque said that the harassment had been so great that it agreed with the owner of the building that he had not to pay rent for the last nine months.
The Guardia Urbana (urban police) also confirmed that it had received more complaints from its neighbours in recent weeks.
The president of the PP (Partido Popular - People's Party) in the Barcelona City Council, Alberto Fernández Díaz, called for the building to be cleared immediately and the problems of civil coexistence and the downfall of the district to be tackled.
He explained that only one floor of the building had been occupied before the summer, but that the squatters had penetrated into all floors of the building and almost all apartments in the last months. In some, theft had even occurred.
In this sense, he added that "it is necessary to put an end to impunity and to intervene against the asocial actions in the building."
Yesterday another building in the district of Nou Barris was cleared by the Catalan police.
At 3.30 p.m., the police approached Montral No. 35 after receiving a call from a neighbor who had been watching four people enter the building.
The four were arrested immediately.
Park or mountain?
The architects agree with the invitation to tender, apart from the disputes over the fees.
The urban call for proposals for the 16 gates opens the debate on the importance of Collserola in Barcelona anew.
In the mid-1980s, at the height of the now disappeared Corporación Metropolitana de Barcelona (CMB), this administration published its disdain for the promotion of Collserola.
The brochure described the mountain as a huge park in Barcelona city.
He was even compared in numbers with the Central Park of New York.
With the collapse of the CMB in 1987, the park became the upper limit of Barcelona in the eyes of many, because the capital of Catalonia is one of the few that does not spread in the north-south direction, but upwards (mountains) and downwards (seas).
The classification of Collserolas as a nature park plays with this idea.
Yellowstone with wild boars in the role of the yogi bear was no longer used as a model.
This is how far it was when the city issued a huge invitation to tender in September, consisting of 16 competitions, for further access gates to Collserola.
Undoubtedly, a gate refers to the concept of a park.
Either that's the way it is, or someone's planning on putting gates in the country.
The question arises of itself: Collserola, park or mountain?
The call for proposals is not only from an organizational point of view, but also from a reflection on the city in the mouth of all architects from Barcelona.
It is almost a recurring topic, on which two members of this old caste, who meet in the elevator, can rely.
And precisely this fact provides the basis for one of the rare similarities between what three architects from Barcelona think about it and some university professors who applied for the project.
Miguel Roldán, Daniel Modol and Marta Bayona: The tender is appropriate.
For Roldán "it is necessary to speak after the attack on the coast about the "front on the mountains" as far as the discourse of Ildefons Cerda, which about the green apples, has not been carried out.
"It should be based on the principle that Barcelona's largest park is the beach.
Among other things, because it is easily accessible.
Collserola is more complex," says the architect, for whom the title "Tore of Collserola" contains a "lexical trap": it must not be imagined "as access to a park, but as a limitation of areas in which action must be taken."
Modol, like Roldán and Bayona with urban development experience, sees the proposal as an "intellectual challenge" that carries "some dangers".
Dangers resulting from the "uncertainty that the design of a public space brings with it nowadays" after the experiences of the 1980s, which had their "swan song" in the area of the forum.
The first fear is one's own limitation on what can be built.
"Limiting something always means setting the next step", i.e. exceeding it.
"You have to think about new urban planning tools, because the present [referring to the General Metropolitano (PGM) plan] can lead to a real disaster."
Modol, who adheres more closely to the question, believes that the side of Collserola, which goes towards Vallesana, "can be understood as a park that does not go towards Barcelona", for purely topographical reasons.
Modol recalls that there is already a study by the Patronate de Collserola, which should not be "feeling deaf ears", although he is grateful to the city administration that it has given his body the opportunity to participate in this project "from the very first moment".
He also notes that the proximity of the mountains to the city is the lead letter, which allows architects to participate in the debate, although he expresses his "doubts" as to whether this technical profile should guide the multidisciplinary teams that have been created ("just the right thing," he says) "We architects should only be a tool."
Bayona suggests that the answer to the question in the heading of this article is complex, since the tender conditions lack a global view of Collserola: "16 competitions were advertised in cross-section," he says, "on the axis of the mountain-sea. But there is no longitudinal perspective that looks at the area as a whole."
This, at least in his case, has led him to participate in the 16 competitions.
Otherwise, the program and definition of a project for a gate would collide with that of the architect of the gate.
In his opinion, the city should absolutely guarantee that the strip is equipped directly over the Ronda de Dalt in its entire length, which creates a soft transition between the city and green areas.
Casino awards Jonás Larrazábal, who comes free
After 72 days of silence, the agent of Casino Red freed the brother of the mayor of Monterrey from the trial being waged against him for alleged blackmail.
After 72 days of imprisonment, Manuel Jonás Larrazábal is released after the agent of Casino Red has given him before the Second Criminal Court of the District, which is leading the trial against the brother of the mayor of Monterrey for blackmail.
After the assassination of Casino Royale, Sergio Gil García, the owner of Casino Red, published a series of photos and videos showing Manuel Jonás, who allegedly forced him to pay a sum of money to allow the city administration to operate the betting house in secret.
