"Moleskine has revived an old and almost forgotten object that was regarded as an icon of avant-garde artists until the 20th century," explains Maria Sebregondi, who is now responsible for the brand at Modo Modo.
Success comes in.
Between 2006 and 2010, sales increased by 26% and established themselves with a sales volume of 12.7 million units.
This is far from the usual production of the first years, in which only 3,000 notebooks were designed.
Moleskine crosses the Italian border and is exported to 70 countries, from France to the United States.
