Disheartening?
"No, according to Éric Blanchet, Director-General of the Adapt Association, which organises the "Work Week for the Disabled".
"The progress made within fifteen years is considerable."
"At that time, the unemployment rate was not double, but triple."
"Nevertheless, there is an enormous amount of work to be done."
However, it must be said that many obstacles remain for disabled unemployed people before they get a job.
